<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="13.[189,310,1110,1136]" box="[189,310,1110,1136]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,310,1110,1136]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,310,1110,1136]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[189,1399,1158,1259]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
The smallest species of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Warren" authorityYear="1905" box="[507,603,1158,1184]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Callipia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="balteata">
<emphasis box="[507,603,1158,1184]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">balteata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group, relatively pale and less contrasting patterns of the wings than in the other species. The cornuti of the vesica are much longer than in the other species of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Warren" authorityYear="1905" box="[1302,1398,1195,1221]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Callipia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="balteata">
<emphasis box="[1302,1398,1195,1221]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">balteata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group. COI-barcode: the observed distance to the genetically most similar species (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Warren" authorityYear="1905" box="[1158,1287,1233,1259]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Callipia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="balteata">
<emphasis box="[1158,1287,1233,1259]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">C. balteata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) is 4.3%.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
