<paragraph blockId="13.[189,1398,1926,2027]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis box="[189,410,1926,1952]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Callipia 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thierry-Mieg" authorityYear="1904" box="[293,410,1926,1952]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Callipia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paradisea">paradisea</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
is known from a few specimens only. Wing patterns and structure of male genitalia not easily fitting into any of the other groups, but 
<emphasis box="[766,879,1964,1989]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">vicinaria</emphasis>
group is possibly most closely related. Since no molecular data are available either, 
<emphasis box="[643,795,2001,2027]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">C. paradisea</emphasis>
is provisionally treated separately.
</paragraph>
